 family Cactaceae. It is a low-growing, shrub-like cactus characterized by short, cylindrical stems up to 10 cm in length, with 5-7 ribs and short, fine spines. The stems are green, with a diameter of 2-3 cm and a height of 2-5 cm. The flowers are funnel-shaped, pale yellow in color, and approximately 3-4 cm in length. This variant of Neoporteria curvispina typically produces yellow flowers in the spring and summer months."}